<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10075g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10075g">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10075g"> 75(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> secret</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Montesquieu, le politique, &mdash; pour rester au milieu des hommes du XVIIIe si&egrave;cle, &mdash; para&icirc;t avoir un peu d&apos;humeur contre l&apos;institution des postes: &ldquo;Les conspirations dans l&apos;&Eacute;tat sont devenues difficiles, dit-il, parce que depuis l&apos;invention des postes tous <mark>les secrets</mark> des particuliers sont dans le pouvoir du public.&rdquo; <font color="green">[The prudent Montesquieu&mdash;if we are to remain with men of the 18th Century&mdash;seems to have had some antagonism against the institution of the post: &ldquo;Conspiracies in the State have become difficult&rdquo;, he says, &ldquo;because ever since the intervention of the post, all the secrets of individuals are in the power of the state.&rdquo;]</font> <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) 9</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
